{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899752802,"sessionID":"ses_284209335ffeGezUdA84JigjjI","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdfb525001wIbAleP2zIbP7E","messageID":"msg_d7bdfa642001HJ1Vww5q7LvicN","sessionID":"ses_284209335ffeGezUdA84JigjjI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService and Data Models — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document provides technical implementation details for the `MetadataService` and data models in the AgentCube CLI project. The MetadataService provides persistent storage and validation for agent configuration using YAML files with Pydantic models, while MetadataOptions provides a dataclass for CLI option handling.\n6: \n7: **AR:** AR-025  \n8: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n9: **Language:** Python  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### Component Diagram\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                            CLI Layer                                          │\n21: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n22: │  │   pack command      │    │   build command     │                         │\n23: │  │   (main.py)         │    │   (main.py)         │                         │\n24: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n25: │             │                          │                                     │\n26: │             ▼                          ▼                                     │\n27: │  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n28: │  │   PackRuntime       │    │   BuildRuntime      │                         │\n29: │  │   (pack_runtime)    │    │   (build_runtime)   │                         │\n30: │  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n31: └─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n32:               │                          │\n33:               ▼                          ▼\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │                       Service & Model Layer                                   │\n36: │                                                                              │\n37: │    ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐        │\n38: │    │                    MetadataService                            │        │\n39: │    │                  (metadata_service)                           │        │\n40: │    └──────────────┬────────────────────────────────┬───────────────┘        │\n41: │                   │                                │                        │\n42: │                   ▼                                ▼                        │\n43: │    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n44: │    │    AgentMetadata    │          │   MetadataOptions   │                │\n45: │    │   (Pydantic Model)  │          │     (Dataclass)     │                │\n46: │    └──────────┬──────────┘          └──────────┬──────────┘                │\n47: │               │                                │                            │\n48: │               ▼                                ▼                            │\n49: │    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n50: │    │  agent_metadata.yaml│          │  CLI Option Mapping │                │\n51: │    │  (YAML Persistence) │          │  (Runtime Options)  │                │\n52: │    └─────────────────────┘          └─────────────────────┘                │\n53: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Data Flow\n57: \n58: #### Metadata Load/Save Flow\n59: ```\n60: 1. PackRuntime calls MetadataService.load_metadata()\n61: 2. Service checks for agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml\n62: 3. If not found, creates default AgentMetadata from workspace\n63: 4. CLI options are merged via _apply_option_overrides()\n64: 5. Service validates the metadata (Pydantic validation)\n65: 6. Modified metadata saved via save_metadata()\n66: 7. Written to {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml\n67: ```\n68: \n69: #### Validation Flow\n70: ```\n71: 1. MetadataService.validate_workspace() called\n72: 2. Checks workspace exists and is directory\n73: 3. Language-specific validation:\n74:    - Python: requires at least one *.py file\n75:    - Java: requires pom.xml\n76: 4. Returns True if valid, raises ValueError if invalid\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Module Structure\n82: \n83: ### File Layout\n84: \n85: | Path | Role |\n86: |------|------|\n87: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class + `AgentMetadata` model |\n88: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n89: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package marker |\n90: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for pack operations |\n91: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for build operations |\n92: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for publish operations |\n93: \n94: ### Dependencies\n95: \n96: ```\n97: MetadataService\n98:     ├── AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n99:     ├── yaml (PyYAML)\n100:     ├── pathlib (Path handling)\n101:     └── typing (Type hints)\n102: \n103: AgentMetadata\n104:     ├── pydantic (BaseModel, Field, validators)\n105:     └── typing (Optional, Dict, Any)\n106: \n107: MetadataOptions\n108:     └── dataclasses (dataclass, field)\n109: \n110: PackRuntime/BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime\n111:     └── MetadataService (for persistence)\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## Implementation Details\n117: \n118: ### 1. AgentMetadata (Pydantic Model)\n119: \n120: The `AgentMetadata` class is the core data model for agent configuration, persisted as YAML.\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n124: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n125: \n126: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n127:     \"\"\"Pydantic model for agent metadata configuration.\n128:     \n129:     This model represents the agent_metadata.yaml file structure\n130:     and provides validation for all agent configuration fields.\n131:     \"\"\"\n132:     \n133:     # Required fields\n134:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n135:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n136:     \n137:     # Fields with defaults\n138:     language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n139:     port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n140:     build_mode: str = Field(default=\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n141:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\n142:         default=\"requirements.txt\", \n143:         description=\"Python dependency file\"\n144:     )\n145:     \n146:     # Optional fields\n147:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n148:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n149:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string\")\n150:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n151:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n152:     \n153:     # Registry configuration\n154:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry URL\")\n155:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n156:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n157:     \n158:     # AgentCube URLs\n159:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Workload Manager\")\n160:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Router\")\n161:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for readiness probe\")\n162:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")\n163:     \n164:     # Runtime state\n165:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n166:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Session ID for the agent\")\n167:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n168:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"K8s deployment info\")\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### Field Validators\n172: \n173: ```python\n174:     @field_validator('language')\n175:     @classmethod\n176:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n177:         \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n178:         allowed = ['python', 'java']\n179:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n180:             raise ValueError(f'language must be one of {allowed}')\n181:         return v.lower()\n182:     \n183:     @field_validator('build_mode')\n184:     @classmethod\n185:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n186:         \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n187:         allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n188:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n189:             raise ValueError(f'build_mode must be one of {allowed}')\n190:         return v.lower()\n191:     \n192:     @field_validator('port')\n193:     @classmethod\n194:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n195:         \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n196:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n197:             raise ValueError('port must be between 1 and 65535')\n198:         return v\n199: ```\n200: \n201: #### Model Configuration\n202: \n203: ```python\n204:     class Config:\n205:         \"\"\"Pydantic configuration.\"\"\"\n206:         # Allow population by field name\n207:         populate_by_name = True\n208:         # Validate assignment\n209:         validate_assignment = True\n210:         # Extra fields forbidden\n211:         extra = 'forbid'\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### 2. MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n217: \n218: The `MetadataOptions` dataclass provides a type-safe way to pass CLI options to runtimes.\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n222: from typing import Optional\n223: \n224: @dataclass\n225: class MetadataOptions:\n226:     \"\"\"Dataclass for CLI pack options.\n227:     \n228:     This provides a structured way to pass command-line options\n229:     to PackRuntime and other components.\n230:     \"\"\"\n231:     \n232:     # Agent configuration\n233:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n234:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n235:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n236:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n237:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n238:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n239:     description: Optional[str] = None\n240:     \n241:     # AgentCube URLs\n242:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n243:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n244:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n245:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n246:     \n247:     # Registry configuration\n248:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n249:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n250:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n251:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n252:     \n253:     @classmethod\n254:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n255:         \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from a dictionary.\n256:         \n257:         Args:\n258:             options: Dictionary of options (typically from CLI)\n259:             \n260:         Returns:\n261:             MetadataOptions instance with values from dict\n262:         \"\"\"\n263:         # Filter to only known fields\n264:         known_fields = {f.name for f in cls.__dataclass_fields__.values()}\n265:         filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n266:         return cls(**filtered)\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ### 3. MetadataService\n272: \n273: The `MetadataService` class provides CRUD operations for agent metadata with YAML persistence.\n274: \n275: ```python\n276: import yaml\n277: from pathlib import Path\n278: from typing import Dict, Any, Optional\n279: import logging\n280: \n281: class MetadataService:\n282:     \"\"\"Service class for agent metadata operations.\n283:     \n284:     Provides:\n285:     - Loading metadata from YAML files (with fallback chain)\n286:     - Saving metadata to YAML files\n287:     - Updating metadata fields\n288:     - Validating workspace structure\n289:     \"\"\"\n290:     \n291:     # Filename precedence (highest to lowest)\n292:     METADATA_FILENAMES = ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n293:     \n294:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n295:         self.verbose = verbose\n296:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n297:         if verbose:\n298:             self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n299: ```\n300: \n301: #### Load Metadata\n302: \n303: ```python\n304:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n305:         \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\n306:         \n307:         Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml -> agent.yaml -> metadata.yaml\n308:         If no file exists, creates default metadata from workspace.\n309:         \n310:         Args:\n311:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n312:             \n313:         Returns:\n314:             AgentMetadata instance\n315:             \n316:         Raises:\n317:             ValueError: If workspace doesn't exist or YAML is invalid\n318:         \"\"\"\n319:         self.logger.debug(f\"Loading metadata from {workspace_path}\")\n320:         \n321:         # Find metadata file\n322:         metadata_file = None\n323:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILENAMES:\n324:             candidate = workspace_path / filename\n325:             if candidate.exists():\n326:                 metadata_file = candidate\n327:                 self.logger.debug(f\"Found metadata file: {candidate}\")\n328:                 break\n329:         \n330:         if metadata_file is None:\n331:             self.logger.debug(\"No metadata file found, creating default\")\n332:             return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path)\n333:         \n334:         # Load and parse YAML\n335:         try:\n336:             with open(metadata_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n337:                 data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n338:             \n339:             self.logger.debug(f\"Loaded metadata: {data}\")\n340:             return AgentMetadata(**data)\n341:             \n342:         except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n343:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {metadata_file}: {e}\")\n344:         except Exception as e:\n345:             raise ValueError(f\"Failed to load metadata: {e}\")\n346: ```\n347: \n348: #### Save Metadata\n349: \n350: ```python\n351:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n352:         \"\"\"Save metadata to YAML file.\n353:         \n354:         Always writes to agent_metadata.yaml (canonical filename).\n355:         \n356:         Args:\n357:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n358:             metadata: AgentMetadata to save\n359:             \n360:         Raises:\n361:             ValueError: If save fails\n362:         \"\"\"\n363:         metadata_file = workspace_path / 'agent_metadata.yaml'\n364:         self.logger.debug(f\"Saving metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n365:         \n366:         try:\n367:             # Convert to dict, excluding None values\n368:             data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n369:             \n370:             # Ensure directory exists\n371:             workspace_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n372:             \n373:             # Write YAML\n374:             with open(metadata_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n375:                 yaml.dump(\n376:                     data,\n377:                     f,\n378:                     default_flow_style=False,\n379:                     indent=2,\n380:                     sort_keys=False,\n381:                     allow_unicode=True\n382:                 )\n383:             \n384:             self.logger.info(f\"Saved metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n385:             \n386:         except Exception as e:\n387:             raise ValueError(f\"Failed to save metadata: {e}\")\n388: ```\n389: \n390: #### Update Metadata\n391: \n392: ```python\n393:     def update_metadata(\n394:         self, \n395:         workspace_path: Path, \n396:         updates: Dict[str, Any]\n397:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n398:         \"\"\"Update metadata with new values.\n399:         \n400:         Loads existing metadata, applies updates, and saves.\n401:         \n402:         Args:\n403:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n404:             updates: Dictionary of field updates\n405:             \n406:         Returns:\n407:             Updated AgentMetadata instance\n408:         \"\"\"\n409:         self.logger.debug(f\"Updating metadata with {updates}\")\n410:         \n411:         # Load existing\n412:         metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n413:         \n414:         # Apply updates\n415:         for key, value in updates.items():\n416:             if hasattr(metadata, key):\n417:                 setattr(metadata, key, value)\n418:             else:\n419:                 self.logger.warning(f\"Unknown metadata field: {key}\")\n420:         \n421:         # Re-validate and save\n422:         metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata.model_dump())\n423:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n424:         \n425:         return metadata\n426: ```\n427: \n428: #### Workspace Validation\n429: \n430: ```python\n431:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n432:         \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\n433:         \n434:         Checks:\n435:         - Workspace exists and is a directory\n436:         - Language-specific requirements (Python: *.py files, Java: pom.xml)\n437:         \n438:         Args:\n439:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n440:             \n441:         Returns:\n442:             True if valid\n443:             \n444:         Raises:\n445:             ValueError: If validation fails\n446:         \"\"\"\n447:         self.logger.debug(f\"Validating workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n448:         \n449:         # Check workspace exists\n450:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n451:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n452:         \n453:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n454:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n455:         \n456:         # Load metadata to determine language\n457:         try:\n458:             metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n459:         except ValueError:\n460:             # No metadata, assume Python\n461:             metadata = AgentMetadata(agent_name=workspace_path.name, entrypoint=\"main.py\")\n462:         \n463:         # Language-specific validation\n464:         if metadata.language == 'python':\n465:             self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n466:         elif metadata.language == 'java':\n467:             self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n468:         \n469:         self.logger.debug(\"Workspace validation passed\")\n470:         return True\n471:     \n472:     def _validate_python_workspace(\n473:         self, \n474:         workspace_path: Path, \n475:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n476:     ) -> None:\n477:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n478:         # Check for at least one Python file\n479:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob('*.py'))\n480:         if not py_files:\n481:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n482:         \n483:         self.logger.debug(f\"Found {len(py_files)} Python files\")\n484:     \n485:     def _validate_java_workspace(\n486:         self, \n487:         workspace_path: Path, \n488:         metadata: AgentMetadata\n489:     ) -> None:\n490:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n491:         # Check for pom.xml\n492:         pom_file = workspace_path / 'pom.xml'\n493:         if not pom_file.exists():\n494:             raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n495:         \n496:         self.logger.debug(\"Found pom.xml\")\n497: ```\n498: \n499: #### Default Metadata Creation\n500: \n501: ```python\n502:     def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n503:         \"\"\"Create default metadata from workspace.\n504:         \n505:         Infers agent name from directory name and entrypoint from\n506:         discovered files.\n507:         \n508:         Args:\n509:             workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n510:             \n511:         Returns:\n512:             AgentMetadata with default values\n513:         \"\"\"\n514:         agent_name = workspace_path.name\n515:         \n516:         # Infer entrypoint\n517:         entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, 'python')\n518:         \n519:         metadata = AgentMetadata(\n520:             agent_name=agent_name,\n521:             entrypoint=entrypoint,\n522:             language='python',\n523:         )\n524:         \n525:         self.logger.debug(f\"Created default metadata: {metadata}\")\n526:         return metadata\n527:     \n528:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n529:         \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace contents.\n530:         \n531:         Args:\n532:             workspace_path: Path to workspace\n533:             language: Programming language\n534:             \n535:         Returns:\n536:             Inferred entrypoint command\n537:         \"\"\"\n538:         if language == 'python':\n539:             # Look for common entry points\n540:             for candidate in ['main.py', 'app.py', 'server.py']:\n541:                 if (workspace_path / candidate).exists():\n542:                     return f\"python {candidate}\"\n543:             # Default to main.py\n544:             return \"python main.py\"\n545:         \n546:         elif language == 'java':\n547:             # Look for main class or jar\n548:             return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n549:         \n550:         return \"\"\n551: ```\n552: \n553: ---\n554: \n555: ### 4. Runtime Integration\n556: \n557: The `PackRuntime` integrates with `MetadataService` for the pack workflow:\n558: \n559: ```python\n560: class PackRuntime:\n561:     \"\"\"Runtime class for pack command.\"\"\"\n562:     \n563:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n564:         self.verbose = verbose\n565:         self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n566:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n567:     \n568:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n569:         \"\"\"Pack an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n570:         # Validate workspace structure\n571:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n572:         \n573:         # Load or create metadata\n574:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n575:         \n576:         # Apply CLI option overrides\n577:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n578:         \n579:         # Validate language compatibility\n580:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n581:         \n582:         # Process dependencies\n583:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n584:         \n585:         # Generate Dockerfile\n586:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n587:         \n588:         # Update and save metadata\n589:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n590:         \n591:         return {\n592:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n593:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n594:             \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n595:         }\n596:     \n597:     def _load_or_create_metadata(\n598:         self, \n599:         workspace_path: Path, \n600:         options: Dict[str, Any]\n601:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n602:         \"\"\"Load existing or create new metadata.\"\"\"\n603:         return self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n604:     \n605:     def _apply_option_overrides(\n606:         self, \n607:         metadata: AgentMetadata, \n608:         options: Dict[str, Any]\n609:     ) -> AgentMetadata:\n610:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n611:         updates = {}\n612:         \n613:         # Map CLI options to metadata fields\n614:         option_mapping = {\n615:             'agent_name': 'agent_name',\n616:             'language': 'language',\n617:             'entrypoint': 'entrypoint',\n618:             'port': 'port',\n619:             'build_mode': 'build_mode',\n620:             'description': 'description',\n621:         }\n622:         \n623:         for opt_key, meta_key in option_mapping.items():\n624:             if options.get(opt_key) is not None:\n625:                 updates[meta_key] = options[opt_key]\n626:         \n627:         if updates:\n628:             # Update and re-validate\n629:             for key, value in updates.items():\n630:                 setattr(metadata, key, value)\n631:             metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata.model_dump())\n632:         \n633:         return metadata\n634: ```\n635: \n636: ---\n637: \n638: ## Data Models\n639: \n640: ### AgentMetadata Schema\n641: \n642: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n643: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n644: | `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique identifier for the agent |\n645: | `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n646: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language (`python`/`java`) |\n647: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Exposed port (1-65535) |\n648: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy (`local`/`cloud`) |\n649: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable description |\n650: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n651: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version (e.g., `v1.0.0`) |\n652: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Image info dict |\n653: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Auth configuration |\n654: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependencies file |\n655: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Image registry URL |\n656: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n657: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n658: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent HTTP endpoint |\n659: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager service URL |\n660: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router service URL |\n661: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe path |\n662: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe port |\n663: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | AgentCube-assigned ID |\n664: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session identifier |\n665: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | K8s deployment status |\n666: \n667: ### MetadataOptions Schema\n668: \n669: | Field | Type | Default | CLI Option |\n670: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n671: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--agent-name` |\n672: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `\"python\"` | `--language` |\n673: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--entrypoint` |\n674: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | `--port` |\n675: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `\"local\"` | `--build-mode` |\n676: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | (inferred) |\n677: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--description` |\n678: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n679: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n680: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n681: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | (config) |\n682: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-url` |\n683: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-username` |\n684: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-password` |\n685: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (runtime) |\n686: \n687: ### YAML Output Format\n688: \n689: ```yaml\n690: agent_name: my-agent\n691: language: python\n692: entrypoint: python main.py\n693: port: 8080\n694: build_mode: local\n695: description: My AI agent\n696: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n697: version: v1.0.0\n698: registry_url: registry.example.com\n699: registry_username: \"\"\n700: registry_password: \"\"\n701: workload_manager_url: http://workload-manager:8080\n702: router_url: http://router:8080\n703: readiness_probe_path: /health\n704: readiness_probe_port: 8080\n705: agent_id: agent-abc123\n706: session_id: session-xyz789\n707: agent_endpoint: http://my-agent.default.svc.cluster.local\n708: k8s_deployment:\n709:   deployment_name: my-agent\n710:   service_name: my-agent\n711:   namespace: default\n712:   replicas: 1\n713:   node_port: 30080\n714: ```\n715: \n716: ---\n717: \n718: ## Error Handling\n719: \n720: ### Error Types\n721: \n722: | Error | Exception | Description |\n723: |-------|-----------|-------------|\n724: | Workspace Not Found | `ValueError` | Workspace path doesn't exist |\n725: | Invalid Workspace | `ValueError` | Workspace is not a directory |\n726: | No Python Files | `ValueError` | Python workspace missing .py files |\n727: | No pom.xml | `ValueError` | Java workspace missing pom.xml |\n728: | Invalid YAML | `ValueError` | YAML syntax error |\n729: | Invalid Field Value | `ValueError` | Pydantic validation error |\n730: | Save Failed | `ValueError` | File write error |\n731: \n732: ### Error Patterns\n733: \n734: **Workspace Validation:**\n735: ```python\n736: if not workspace_path.exists():\n737:     raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n738: ```\n739: \n740: **YAML Loading:**\n741: ```python\n742: try:\n743:     with open(metadata_file, 'r') as f:\n744:         data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n745: except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n746:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML: {e}\")\n747: ```\n748: \n749: **Pydantic Validation:**\n750: ```python\n751: try:\n752:     metadata = AgentMetadata(**data)\n753: except ValidationError as e:\n754:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid metadata: {e}\")\n755: ```\n756: \n757: ---\n758: \n759: ## Configuration\n760: \n761: ### Environment Variables\n762: \n763: | Variable | Used For |\n764: |----------|----------|\n765: | `AGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Default Workload Manager URL |\n766: | `AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_URL` | Default Router URL |\n767: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_URL` | Default image registry URL |\n768: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | Default registry username |\n769: | `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | Default registry password |\n770: \n771: ### File Locations\n772: \n773: | File | Purpose |\n774: |------|---------|\n775: | `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` | Canonical metadata file (read/write) |\n776: | `{workspace}/agent.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n777: | `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n778: | `~/.agentcube/config.yaml` | User configuration (optional) |\n779: \n780: ---\n781: \n782: ## Testing Strategy\n783: \n784: ### Unit Tests\n785: \n786: 1. **AgentMetadata tests**:\n787:    - `test_valid_metadata` - Create valid metadata\n788:    - `test_language_validation` - Test language validator\n789:    - `test_build_mode_validation` - Test build_mode validator\n790:    - `test_port_validation` - Test port range validation\n791:    - `test_invalid_language` - Error on bad language\n792:    - `test_invalid_port` - Error on out-of-range port\n793:    - `test_serialization` - YAML serialization round-trip\n794: \n795: 2. **MetadataOptions tests**:\n796:    - `test_defaults` - Default values\n797:    - `test_from_options` - Create from dict\n798:    - `test_from_options_ignores_unknown` - Unknown keys ignored\n799: \n800: 3. **MetadataService tests**:\n801:    - `test_load_existing_metadata` - Load from file\n802:    - `test_load_with_fallback` - Fallback filename\n803:    - `test_load_creates_default` - Create if missing\n804:    - `test_save_metadata` - Write to file\n805:    - `test_update_metadata` - Update and save\n806:    - `test_validate_workspace_success` - Valid workspace\n807:    - `test_validate_workspace_not_exist` - Missing workspace\n808:    - `test_validate_python_no_files` - Python validation\n809:    - `test_validate_java_no_pom` - Java validation\n810: \n811: ### Mock Strategy\n812: \n813: ```python\n814: @pytest.fixture\n815: def temp_workspace(tmp_path):\n816:     \"\"\"Create a temporary workspace.\"\"\"\n817:     workspace = tmp_path / \"test-agent\"\n818:     workspace.mkdir()\n819:     (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n820:     return workspace\n821: \n822: def test_load_existing_metadata(temp_workspace):\n823:     # Create metadata file\n824:     metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n825:     metadata_file.write_text(\"\"\"\n826: agent_name: test-agent\n827: entrypoint: python main.py\n828: language: python\n829: \"\"\")\n830:     \n831:     service = MetadataService()\n832:     metadata = service.load_metadata(temp_workspace)\n833:     \n834:     assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n835:     assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n836: \n837: def test_save_metadata(temp_workspace):\n838:     service = MetadataService()\n839:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n840:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n841:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\"\n842:     )\n843:     \n844:     service.save_metadata(temp_workspace, metadata)\n845:     \n846:     # Verify file exists\n847:     metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n848:     assert metadata_file.exists()\n849:     \n850:     # Verify content\n851:     data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n852:     assert data['agent_name'] == \"test-agent\"\n853: ```\n854: \n855: ### Integration Tests\n856: \n857: 1. **Full Pack Flow**:\n858:    - Create workspace with Python files\n859:    - Run pack with options\n860:    - Verify metadata.yaml created\n861:    - Verify options applied\n862: \n863: 2. **Language Detection**:\n864:    - Python workspace detection\n865:    - Java workspace detection\n866:    - Entrypoint inference\n867: \n868: 3. **YAML Round-trip**:\n869:    - Create metadata\n870:    - Save to YAML\n871:    - Load from YAML\n872:    - Verify fields preserved\n873: \n874: ---\n875: \n876: ## Security Considerations\n877: \n878: 1. **Registry Credentials**:\n879:    - Passwords stored in metadata.yaml (workspace-local)\n880:    - Environment variables preferred for CI/CD\n881:    - Support for credential helpers\n882: \n883: 2. **File Permissions**:\n884:    - Metadata files created with user-only permissions (0o600)\n885:    - Workspace directory permissions checked\n886: \n887: 3. **Path Traversal**:\n888:    - All paths resolved relative to workspace\n889:    - No absolute path writes outside workspace\n890:    - Sanitization of agent_name for filenames\n891: \n892: 4. **Secret Redaction**:\n893:    - registry_password excluded from verbose logging\n894:    - auth dict fields masked in output\n895: \n896: ---\n897: \n898: ## Performance Characteristics\n899: \n900: | Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n901: |-----------|------------------|-------|\n902: | Load metadata | <10ms | YAML parsing |\n903: | Save metadata | <10ms | YAML serialization |\n904: | Validate workspace | <50ms | File system checks |\n905: | Create default | <5ms | In-memory only |\n906: \n907: ### Optimization Strategies\n908: \n909: 1. **Lazy Loading**: Metadata loaded only when needed\n910: 2. **Caching**: Runtime holds metadata reference\n911: 3. **Minimal I/O**: Single file read/write per operation\n912: 4. **Efficient YAML**: sort_keys=False preserves field order\n913: \n914: ---\n915: \n916: ## Dependencies\n917: \n918: ### External Dependencies\n919: \n920: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n921: |---------|---------|---------|\n922: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation and serialization |\n923: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML parsing and generation |\n924: | `dataclasses` | (builtin) | Options dataclass |\n925: \n926: ### Python Requirements\n927: \n928: ```toml\n929: [project]\n930: dependencies = [\n931:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n932:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n933:     # ... other deps\n934: ]\n935: ```\n936: \n937: ---\n938: \n939: ## References\n940: \n941: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n942: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n943: - [Pydantic Documentation](https://docs.pydantic.dev/) - Pydantic model docs\n944: - [PyYAML Documentation](https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation) - YAML library docs\n\n(End of file - total 944 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService and Data Models — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `MetadataService` and data models in the AgentCube CLI project. The MetadataService provides persistent storage and validation for agent configuration using YAML files with Pydantic models, while MetadataOptions provides a dataclass for CLI option handling.\n\n**AR:** AR-025  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            CLI Layer                                          │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775899752780,"end":1775899752798}}}}
