to omit null values | Unit test: None values not written to YAML | 0.5h |\n59: | 4.3.7 | Implement `update_metadata()` for load-update-save cycle | Unit test: updates applied and persisted to file | 1h |\n60: \n61: **Deliverable:** Core CRUD operations for metadata persistence.\n62: \n63: **Files:**\n64: - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - MetadataService class\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## ST-4.4 — MetadataService Workspace Validation\n69: \n70: ### Tasks\n71: \n72: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n73: |---|------|--------------|------|\n74: | 4.4.1 | Implement `validate_workspace()` checking workspace exists and is directory | Unit test: non-existent path raises ValueError, file path raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n75: | 4.4.2 | Implement `validate_workspace()` dispatching to language-specific validators | Unit test: python calls _validate_python_workspace, java calls _validate_java_workspace | 0.5h |\n76: | 4.4.3 | Implement `_validate_python_workspace()` requiring at least one *.py file | Unit test: workspace with .py passes, without raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n77: | 4.4.4 | Implement `_validate_java_workspace()` requiring pom.xml | Unit test: workspace with pom.xml passes, without raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n78: \n79: **Deliverable:** Workspace validation for Python and Java agents.\n80: \n81: **Files:**\n82: - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - validation methods\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## ST-4.5 — MetadataService Default Metadata Creation\n87: \n88: ### Tasks\n89: \n90: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n91: |---|------|--------------|------|\n92: | 4.5.1 | Implement `_create_default_metadata()` inferring agent_name from directory name | Unit test: /path/to/my-agent → agent_name=\"my-agent\" | 0.5h |\n93: | 4.5.2 | Implement `_infer_entrypoint()` for Python workspaces | Unit test: finds main.py, app.py, server.py in priority order | 1h |\n94: | 4.5.3 | Implement `_infer_entrypoint()` defaulting to \"python main.py\" when no candidate found |