{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900239041,"sessionID":"ses_284209335ffeGezUdA84JigjjI","part":{"id":"prt_d7be0b4f3001f5TB2Qf3Vrur2t","messageID":"msg_d7be05931001SADdnm2wytcEAw","sessionID":"ses_284209335ffeGezUdA84JigjjI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","content":"# AR-025: MetadataService and Data Models — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the `MetadataService` and data models in the AgentCube CLI project. The MetadataService provides persistent storage and validation for agent configuration using YAML files with Pydantic models, while MetadataOptions provides a dataclass for CLI option handling.\n\n**AR:** AR-025  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            CLI Layer                                          │\n│  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n│  │   pack command      │    │   build command     │                         │\n│  │   (main.py)         │    │   (main.py)         │                         │\n│  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n│             │                          │                                     │\n│             ▼                          ▼                                     │\n│  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                         │\n│  │   PackRuntime       │    │   BuildRuntime      │                         │\n│  │   (pack_runtime)    │    │   (build_runtime)   │                         │\n│  └──────────┬──────────┘    └──────────┬──────────┘                         │\n└─────────────┼──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┘\n              │                          │\n              ▼                          ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       Service & Model Layer                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│    ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐        │\n│    │                    MetadataService                            │        │\n│    │                  (metadata_service)                           │        │\n│    └──────────────┬────────────────────────────────┬───────────────┘        │\n│                   │                                │                        │\n│                   ▼                                ▼                        │\n│    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n│    │    AgentMetadata    │          │   MetadataOptions   │                │\n│    │   (Pydantic Model)  │          │     (Dataclass)     │                │\n│    └──────────┬──────────┘          └──────────┬──────────┘                │\n│               │                                │                            │\n│               ▼                                ▼                            │\n│    ┌─────────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────────┐                │\n│    │  agent_metadata.yaml│          │  CLI Option Mapping │                │\n│    │  (YAML Persistence) │          │  (Runtime Options)  │                │\n│    └─────────────────────┘          └─────────────────────┘                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n#### Metadata Load/Save Flow\n```\n1. PackRuntime calls MetadataService.load_metadata()\n2. Service checks for agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml\n3. If not found, creates default AgentMetadata from workspace\n4. CLI options are merged via _apply_option_overrides()\n5. Service validates the metadata (Pydantic validation)\n6. Modified metadata saved via save_metadata()\n7. Written to {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml\n```\n\n#### Validation Flow\n```\n1. MetadataService.validate_workspace() called\n2. Checks workspace exists and is directory\n3. Language-specific validation:\n   - Python: requires at least one *.py file\n   - Java: requires pom.xml\n4. Returns True if valid, raises ValueError if invalid\n```\n\n---\n\n## Module Structure\n\n### File Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class + `AgentMetadata` model |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package marker |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for pack operations |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for build operations |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses MetadataService for publish operations |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```\nMetadataService\n    ├── AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n    ├── yaml (PyYAML)\n    ├── pathlib (Path handling)\n    └── typing (Type hints)\n\nAgentMetadata\n    ├── pydantic (BaseModel, Field, validators)\n    └── typing (Optional, Dict, Any)\n\nMetadataOptions\n    └── dataclasses (dataclass, field)\n\nPackRuntime/BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime\n    └── MetadataService (for persistence)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. AgentMetadata (Pydantic Model)\n\nThe `AgentMetadata` class is the core data model for agent configuration, persisted as YAML.\n\n```python\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\nfrom typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Pydantic model for agent metadata configuration.\n    \n    This model represents the agent_metadata.yaml file structure\n    and provides validation for all agent configuration fields.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # Required fields\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    \n    # Fields with defaults\n    language: str = Field(default=\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    port: int = Field(default=8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(default=\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\n        default=\"requirements.txt\", \n        description=\"Python dependency file\"\n    )\n    \n    # Optional fields\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string\")\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    \n    # Registry configuration\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry URL\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(default=\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    \n    # AgentCube URLs\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for Router\")\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")\n    \n    # Runtime state\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Session ID for the agent\")\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"K8s deployment info\")\n```\n\n#### Field Validators\n\n```python\n    @field_validator('language')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n        allowed = ['python', 'java']\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f'language must be one of {allowed}')\n        return v.lower()\n    \n    @field_validator('build_mode')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Validate build mode is supported.\"\"\"\n        allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n        if v.lower() not in allowed:\n            raise ValueError(f'build_mode must be one of {allowed}')\n        return v.lower()\n    \n    @field_validator('port')\n    @classmethod\n    def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Validate port is in valid range.\"\"\"\n        if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n            raise ValueError('port must be between 1 and 65535')\n        return v\n```\n\n#### Model Configuration\n\n```python\n    class Config:\n        \"\"\"Pydantic configuration.\"\"\"\n        # Allow population by field name\n        populate_by_name = True\n        # Validate assignment\n        validate_assignment = True\n        # Extra fields forbidden\n        extra = 'forbid'\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n\nThe `MetadataOptions` dataclass provides a type-safe way to pass CLI options to runtimes.\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"Dataclass for CLI pack options.\n    \n    This provides a structured way to pass command-line options\n    to PackRuntime and other components.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # Agent configuration\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    \n    # AgentCube URLs\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    \n    # Registry configuration\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create MetadataOptions from a dictionary.\n        \n        Args:\n            options: Dictionary of options (typically from CLI)\n            \n        Returns:\n            MetadataOptions instance with values from dict\n        \"\"\"\n        # Filter to only known fields\n        known_fields = {f.name for f in cls.__dataclass_fields__.values()}\n        filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n        return cls(**filtered)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. MetadataService\n\nThe `MetadataService` class provides CRUD operations for agent metadata with YAML persistence.\n\n```python\nimport yaml\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nimport logging\n\nclass MetadataService:\n    \"\"\"Service class for agent metadata operations.\n    \n    Provides:\n    - Loading metadata from YAML files (with fallback chain)\n    - Saving metadata to YAML files\n    - Updating metadata fields\n    - Validating workspace structure\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # Filename precedence (highest to lowest)\n    METADATA_FILENAMES = ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n    \n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        if verbose:\n            self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n```\n\n#### Load Metadata\n\n```python\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\n        \n        Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml -> agent.yaml -> metadata.yaml\n        If no file exists, creates default metadata from workspace.\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n            \n        Returns:\n            AgentMetadata instance\n            \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If workspace doesn't exist or YAML is invalid\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.debug(f\"Loading metadata from {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        # Find metadata file\n        metadata_file = None\n        for filename in self.METADATA_FILENAMES:\n            candidate = workspace_path / filename\n            if candidate.exists():\n                metadata_file = candidate\n                self.logger.debug(f\"Found metadata file: {candidate}\")\n                break\n        \n        if metadata_file is None:\n            self.logger.debug(\"No metadata file found, creating default\")\n            return self._create_default_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Load and parse YAML\n        try:\n            with open(metadata_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n            \n            self.logger.debug(f\"Loaded metadata: {data}\")\n            return AgentMetadata(**data)\n            \n        except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {metadata_file}: {e}\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Failed to load metadata: {e}\")\n```\n\n#### Save Metadata\n\n```python\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to YAML file.\n        \n        Always writes to agent_metadata.yaml (canonical filename).\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n            metadata: AgentMetadata to save\n            \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If save fails\n        \"\"\"\n        metadata_file = workspace_path / 'agent_metadata.yaml'\n        self.logger.debug(f\"Saving metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n        \n        try:\n            # Convert to dict, excluding None values\n            data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n            \n            # Ensure directory exists\n            workspace_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n            \n            # Write YAML\n            with open(metadata_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                yaml.dump(\n                    data,\n                    f,\n                    default_flow_style=False,\n                    indent=2,\n                    sort_keys=False,\n                    allow_unicode=True\n                )\n            \n            self.logger.info(f\"Saved metadata to {metadata_file}\")\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Failed to save metadata: {e}\")\n```\n\n#### Update Metadata\n\n```python\n    def update_metadata(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        updates: Dict[str, Any]\n    ) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Update metadata with new values.\n        \n        Loads existing metadata, applies updates, and saves.\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n            updates: Dictionary of field updates\n            \n        Returns:\n            Updated AgentMetadata instance\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.debug(f\"Updating metadata with {updates}\")\n        \n        # Load existing\n        metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        \n        # Apply updates\n        for key, value in updates.items():\n            if hasattr(metadata, key):\n                setattr(metadata, key, value)\n            else:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Unknown metadata field: {key}\")\n        \n        # Re-validate and save\n        metadata = AgentMetadata(**metadata.model_dump())\n        self.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        return metadata\n```\n\n#### Workspace Validation\n\n```python\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace structure.\n        \n        Checks:\n        - Workspace exists and is a directory\n        - Language-specific requirements (Python: *.py files, Java: pom.xml)\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n            \n        Returns:\n            True if valid\n            \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If validation fails\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.debug(f\"Validating workspace: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        # Check workspace exists\n        if not workspace_path.exists():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n            raise ValueError(f\"Workspace is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n        \n        # Load metadata to determine language\n        try:\n            metadata = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        except ValueError:\n            # No metadata, assume Python\n            metadata = AgentMetadata(agent_name=workspace_path.name, entrypoint=\"main.py\")\n        \n        # Language-specific validation\n        if metadata.language == 'python':\n            self._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        elif metadata.language == 'java':\n            self._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)\n        \n        self.logger.debug(\"Workspace validation passed\")\n        return True\n    \n    def _validate_python_workspace(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        metadata: AgentMetadata\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n        # Check for at least one Python file\n        py_files = list(workspace_path.glob('*.py'))\n        if not py_files:\n            raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n        \n        self.logger.debug(f\"Found {len(py_files)} Python files\")\n    \n    def _validate_java_workspace(\n        self, \n        workspace_path: Path, \n        metadata: AgentMetadata\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n        # Check for pom.xml\n        pom_file = workspace_path / 'pom.xml'\n        if not pom_file.exists():\n            raise ValueError(\"Java workspace requires pom.xml\")\n        \n        self.logger.debug(\"Found pom.xml\")\n```\n\n#### Default Metadata Creation\n\n```python\n    def _create_default_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Create default metadata from workspace.\n        \n        Infers agent name from directory name and entrypoint from\n        discovered files.\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n            \n        Returns:\n            AgentMetadata with default values\n        \"\"\"\n        agent_name = workspace_path.name\n        \n        # Infer entrypoint\n        entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, 'python')\n        \n        metadata = AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=agent_name,\n            entrypoint=entrypoint,\n            language='python',\n        )\n        \n        self.logger.debug(f\"Created default metadata: {metadata}\")\n        return metadata\n    \n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Infer entrypoint from workspace contents.\n        \n        Args:\n            workspace_path: Path to workspace\n            language: Programming language\n            \n        Returns:\n            Inferred entrypoint command\n        \"\"\"\n        if language == 'python':\n            # Look for common entry points\n            for candidate in ['main.py', 'app.py', 'server.py']:\n                if (workspace_path / candidate).exists():\n                    return f\"python {candidate}\"\n            # Default to main.py\n            return \"python main.py\"\n        \n        elif language == 'java':\n            # Look for main class or jar\n            return \"java -jar app.jar\"\n        \n        return \"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Models\n\n### AgentMetadata Schema\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique identifier for the agent |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language (`python`/`java`) |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Exposed port (1-65535) |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy (`local`/`cloud`) |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable description |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version (e.g., `v1.0.0`) |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Image info dict |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Auth configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependencies file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Image registry URL |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent HTTP endpoint |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe path |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | K8s readiness probe port |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | AgentCube-assigned ID |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session identifier |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | K8s deployment status |\n\n### MetadataOptions Schema\n\n| Field | Type | Default | CLI Option |\n|-------|------|---------|------------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--agent-name` |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `\"python\"` | `--language` |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--entrypoint` |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | `--port` |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `\"local\"` | `--build-mode` |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | (inferred) |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | `--description` |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (config) |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` | (config) |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-url` |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-username` |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | `--image-password` |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | (runtime) |\n\n### YAML Output Format\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\ndescription: My AI agent\nrequirements_file: requirements.txt\nversion: v1.0.0\nregistry_url: registry.example.com\nregistry_username: \"\"\nregistry_password: \"\"\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager:8080\nrouter_url: http://router:8080\nreadiness_probe_path: /health\nreadiness_probe_port: 8080\nagent_id: agent-abc123\nsession_id: session-xyz789\nagent_endpoint: http://my-agent.default.svc.cluster.local\nk8s_deployment:\n  deployment_name: my-agent\n  service_name: my-agent\n  namespace: default\n  replicas: 1\n  node_port: 30080\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Exception | Description |\n|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| Workspace Not Found | `ValueError` | Workspace path doesn't exist |\n| Invalid Workspace | `ValueError` | Workspace is not a directory |\n| No Python Files | `ValueError` | Python workspace missing .py files |\n| No pom.xml | `ValueError` | Java workspace missing pom.xml |\n| Invalid YAML | `ValueError` | YAML syntax error |\n| Invalid Field Value | `ValueError` | Pydantic validation error |\n| Save Failed | `ValueError` | File write error |\n\n### Error Patterns\n\n**Workspace Validation:**\n```python\nif not workspace_path.exists():\n    raise ValueError(f\"Workspace does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n```\n\n**YAML Loading:**\n```python\ntry:\n    with open(metadata_file, 'r') as f:\n        data = yaml.safe_load(f)\nexcept yaml.YAMLError as e:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML: {e}\")\n```\n\n**Pydantic Validation:**\n```python\ntry:\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(**data)\nexcept ValidationError as e:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Invalid metadata: {e}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used For |\n|----------|----------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Default Workload Manager URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_URL` | Default Router URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_URL` | Default image registry URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | Default registry username |\n| `AGENTCUBE_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | Default registry password |\n\n### File Locations\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` | Canonical metadata file (read/write) |\n| `{workspace}/agent.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n| `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` | Fallback read location |\n| `~/.agentcube/config.yaml` | User configuration (optional) |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **AgentMetadata tests**:\n   - `test_valid_metadata` - Create valid metadata\n   - `test_language_validation` - Test language validator\n   - `test_build_mode_validation` - Test build_mode validator\n   - `test_port_validation` - Test port range validation\n   - `test_invalid_language` - Error on bad language\n   - `test_invalid_port` - Error on out-of-range port\n   - `test_serialization` - YAML serialization round-trip\n\n2. **MetadataOptions tests**:\n   - `test_defaults` - Default values\n   - `test_from_options` - Create from dict\n   - `test_from_options_ignores_unknown` - Unknown keys ignored\n\n3. **MetadataService tests**:\n   - `test_load_existing_metadata` - Load from file\n   - `test_load_with_fallback` - Fallback filename\n   - `test_load_creates_default` - Create if missing\n   - `test_save_metadata` - Write to file\n   - `test_update_metadata` - Update and save\n   - `test_validate_workspace_success` - Valid workspace\n   - `test_validate_workspace_not_exist` - Missing workspace\n   - `test_validate_python_no_files` - Python validation\n   - `test_validate_java_no_pom` - Java validation\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef temp_workspace(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Create a temporary workspace.\"\"\"\n    workspace = tmp_path / \"test-agent\"\n    workspace.mkdir()\n    (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n    return workspace\n\ndef test_load_existing_metadata(temp_workspace):\n    # Create metadata file\n    metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    metadata_file.write_text(\"\"\"\nagent_name: test-agent\nentrypoint: python main.py\nlanguage: python\n\"\"\")\n    \n    service = MetadataService()\n    metadata = service.load_metadata(temp_workspace)\n    \n    assert metadata.agent_name == \"test-agent\"\n    assert metadata.entrypoint == \"python main.py\"\n\ndef test_save_metadata(temp_workspace):\n    service = MetadataService()\n    metadata = AgentMetadata(\n        agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n        entrypoint=\"python main.py\"\n    )\n    \n    service.save_metadata(temp_workspace, metadata)\n    \n    # Verify file exists\n    metadata_file = temp_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    assert metadata_file.exists()\n    \n    # Verify content\n    data = yaml.safe_load(metadata_file.read_text())\n    assert data['agent_name'] == \"test-agent\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Full Pack Flow**:\n   - Create workspace with Python files\n   - Run pack with options\n   - Verify metadata.yaml created\n   - Verify options applied\n\n2. **Language Detection**:\n   - Python workspace detection\n   - Java workspace detection\n   - Entrypoint inference\n\n3. **YAML Round-trip**:\n   - Create metadata\n   - Save to YAML\n   - Load from YAML\n   - Verify fields preserved\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Registry Credentials**:\n   - Passwords stored in metadata.yaml (workspace-local)\n   - Environment variables preferred for CI/CD\n   - Support for credential helpers\n\n2. **File Permissions**:\n   - Metadata files created with user-only permissions (0o600)\n   - Workspace directory permissions checked\n\n3. **Path Traversal**:\n   - All paths resolved relative to workspace\n   - No absolute path writes outside workspace\n   - Sanitization of agent_name for filenames\n\n4. **Secret Redaction**:\n   - registry_password excluded from verbose logging\n   - auth dict fields masked in output\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n|-----------|------------------|-------|\n| Load metadata | <10ms | YAML parsing |\n| Save metadata | <10ms | YAML serialization |\n| Validate workspace | <50ms | File system checks |\n| Create default | <5ms | In-memory only |\n\n### Optimization Strategies\n\n1. **Lazy Loading**: Metadata loaded only when needed\n2. **Caching**: Runtime holds metadata reference\n3. **Minimal I/O**: Single file read/write per operation\n4. **Efficient YAML**: sort_keys=False preserves field order\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation and serialization |\n| `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML parsing and generation |\n| `dataclasses` | (builtin) | Options dataclass |\n\n### Python Requirements\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    # ... other deps\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n- [Pydantic Documentation](https://docs.pydantic.dev/) - Pydantic model docs\n- [PyYAML Documentation](https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation) - YAML library docs\n\n---\n\n---\n\n# AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for the Kubernetes deployment providers in the AgentCube CLI project. The `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes environments using either standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource.\n\n**AR:** AR-026  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Provider Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Provider Architecture                                 │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┐              ┌──────────────────────┐            │\n│  │   KubernetesProvider │              │  AgentCubeProvider   │            │\n│  │   (Standard K8s)     │              │  (AgentRuntime CR)   │            │\n│  │                      │              │                      │            │\n│  │  • Deployment        │              │  • AgentRuntime CR   │            │\n│  │  • NodePort Service  │              │  • Readiness Probes  │            │\n│  │  • Replicas          │              │  • Session Mgmt      │            │\n│  │  • NodePort (opt)    │              │  • Router/WM URLs    │            │\n│  └──────────┬───────────┘              └──────────┬───────────┘            │\n│             │                                      │                        │\n│             └──────────────┬───────────────────────┘                        │\n│                            │                                                │\n│                            ▼                                                │\n│              ┌─────────────────────────┐                                    │\n│              │   Kubernetes Client     │                                    │\n│              │   (lazy initialization) │                                    │\n│              └─────────────────────────┘                                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Deployment Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Standard K8s Deployment Flow                              │\n│                                                                              │\n│  deploy_agent()                                                             │\n│       │                                                                      │\n│       ▼                                                                      │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Validate NodePort│──► ValueError (if outside 30000-32767)               │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Get K8s Client   │──► RuntimeError (if k8s unavailable)                 │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Ensure Namespace │──► Creates if missing                                 │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│     ┌─────┴─────┐                                                            │\n│     ▼           ▼                                                            │\n│  ┌──────┐   ┌────────┐                                                       │\n│  │Deploy│   │Service │──► Create/Update resources                            │\n│  └──────┘   └────────┘                                                       │\n│     │           │                                                            │\n│     └─────┬─────┘                                                            │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Return Result    │──► deployment_name, service_name, node_port, etc     │\n│  └──────────────────┘                                                       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     AgentRuntime CR Deployment Flow                           │\n│                                                                              │\n│  deploy_agent_runtime()                                                     │\n│       │                                                                      │\n│       ▼                                                                      │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Validate URLs    │──► ValueError (if router_url or wm_url missing)      │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Get K8s Client   │                                                       │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Ensure Namespace │                                                       │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Build CR Spec    │──► Create spec dict with env vars, probes, etc      │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Apply CR         │──► Create/Update AgentRuntime via CustomObjectsApi  │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘                                                       │\n│           │                                                                  │\n│           ▼                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐                                                       │\n│  │ Return Result    │──► agent_id, agent_endpoint, status                  │\n│  └──────────────────┘                                                       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Module Structure\n\n### File Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Service exports |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses providers for publish |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Uses providers for invoke |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Uses providers for status |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```\nKubernetesProvider\n    ├── kubernetes (AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api)\n    ├── config (load_kube_config, load_incluster_config)\n    └── typing (Dict, Any, Optional)\n\nAgentCubeProvider\n    ├── kubernetes (CustomObjectsApi)\n    ├── KubernetesProvider (shared client pattern)\n    └── typing (Dict, Any, Optional)\n\nRuntime Integration\n    ├── PublishRuntime (publish command)\n    ├── InvokeRuntime (invoke command)\n    └── StatusRuntime (status command)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. KubernetesProvider\n\nThe `KubernetesProvider` class deploys agents using standard Kubernetes resources.\n\n```python\nfrom kubernetes import client, config\nfrom kubernetes.client.exceptions import ApiException\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nimport logging\nimport time\n\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for standard Kubernetes deployments.\n    \n    Creates Deployment and NodePort Service resources for agent deployment.\n    Supports configurable replicas, environment variables, and optional NodePort.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the Kubernetes provider.\n        \n        Args:\n            namespace: Default namespace for resources\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging\n            kubeconfig: Path to kubeconfig file (optional)\n        \"\"\"\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        self._k8s_client = None\n        \n        if verbose:\n            self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n```\n\n#### Lazy Client Initialization\n\n```python\n    def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client with config fallback.\n        \n        Tries to load kubeconfig from:\n        1. Explicit kubeconfig path if provided\n        2. Default kubeconfig location\n        3. In-cluster configuration (for running inside K8s)\n        \n        Returns:\n            Kubernetes client APIs tuple\n            \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If kubernetes library not installed or config fails\n        \"\"\"\n        if self._k8s_client is not None:\n            return self._k8s_client\n        \n        try:\n            from kubernetes import client, config\n        except ImportError:\n            raise RuntimeError(\n                \"Kubernetes client library not installed. \"\n                \"Install with: pip install kubernetes\"\n            )\n        \n        # Try to load configuration\n        try:\n            if self.kubeconfig:\n                config.load_kube_config(config_file=self.kubeconfig)\n                self.logger.debug(f\"Loaded kubeconfig from {self.kubeconfig}\")\n            else:\n                config.load_kube_config()\n                self.logger.debug(\"Loaded default kubeconfig\")\n        except Exception:\n            # Fallback to in-cluster config\n            try:\n                config.load_incluster_config()\n                self.logger.debug(\"Loaded in-cluster config\")\n            except Exception as e:\n                raise RuntimeError(\n                    f\"Failed to load Kubernetes configuration: {e}\"\n                )\n        \n        # Initialize API clients\n        self._k8s_client = {\n            'apps': client.AppsV1Api(),\n            'core': client.CoreV1Api(),\n            'custom': client.CustomObjectsApi(),\n        }\n        \n        return self._k8s_client\n```\n\n#### Namespace Management\n\n```python\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists, create if missing.\n        \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If namespace creation fails\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        core_api = k8s['core']\n        \n        try:\n            core_api.read_namespace(self.namespace)\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Namespace {self.namespace} exists\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                # Create namespace\n                try:\n                    namespace_body = client.V1Namespace(\n                        metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(name=self.namespace)\n                    )\n                    core_api.create_namespace(namespace_body)\n                    self.logger.info(f\"Created namespace: {self.namespace}\")\n                except Exception as create_err:\n                    raise RuntimeError(\n                        f\"Failed to create namespace {self.namespace}: {create_err}\"\n                    )\n            else:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to check namespace: {e}\")\n```\n\n#### Deploy Agent\n\n```python\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy agent as Deployment + NodePort Service.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name for the agent (used for resource naming)\n            image_url: Container image URL\n            port: Container port to expose\n            entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command override\n            replicas: Number of pod replicas\n            node_port: Optional specific NodePort (30000-32767)\n            env_vars: Optional environment variables dict\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deployment info including:\n            - deployment_name, service_name, namespace\n            - node_port, service_url\n            - replicas, container_port\n            - status: \"deployed\"\n            \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If node_port is outside valid range\n            RuntimeError: If deployment fails\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.info(f\"Deploying agent {agent_name} to namespace {self.namespace}\")\n        \n        # Validate node_port if provided\n        if node_port is not None:\n            if not (30000 <= node_port <= 32767):\n                raise ValueError(\n                    f\"NodePort must be in range 30000-32767, got {node_port}\"\n                )\n        \n        # Ensure namespace exists\n        self._ensure_namespace()\n        \n        # Create deployment\n        deployment_result = self._create_deployment(\n            name=agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=port,\n            entrypoint=entrypoint,\n            replicas=replicas,\n            env_vars=env_vars,\n        )\n        \n        # Create service\n        service_result = self._create_service(\n            name=agent_name,\n            port=port,\n            node_port=node_port,\n        )\n        \n        # Build result\n        result = {\n            \"deployment_name\": deployment_result['name'],\n            \"service_name\": service_result['name'],\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n            \"container_port\": port,\n            \"node_port\": service_result['node_port'],\n            \"service_url\": f\"http://localhost:{service_result['node_port']}\",\n            \"status\": \"deployed\",\n        }\n        \n        self.logger.info(f\"Agent {agent_name} deployed successfully\")\n        return result\n```\n\n#### Create Deployment\n\n```python\n    def _create_deployment(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        replicas: int,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create or update Deployment resource.\n        \n        Args:\n            name: Deployment name\n            image_url: Container image\n            port: Container port\n            entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command\n            replicas: Number of replicas\n            env_vars: Environment variables\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deployment info\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        apps_api = k8s['apps']\n        \n        # Build container spec\n        container = client.V1Container(\n            name=name,\n            image=image_url,\n            ports=[client.V1ContainerPort(container_port=port)],\n        )\n        \n        # Add entrypoint if provided\n        if entrypoint:\n            parts = entrypoint.split()\n            container.command = [parts[0]] if parts else []\n            container.args = parts[1:] if len(parts) > 1 else []\n        \n        # Add environment variables\n        if env_vars:\n            container.env = [\n                client.V1EnvVar(name=k, value=v)\n                for k, v in env_vars.items()\n            ]\n        \n        # Build pod template\n        template = client.V1PodTemplateSpec(\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(labels={\"app\": name}),\n            spec=client.V1PodSpec(\n                containers=[container],\n            ),\n        )\n        \n        # Build deployment spec\n        deployment_spec = client.V1DeploymentSpec(\n            replicas=replicas,\n            selector={\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": name}},\n            template=template,\n        )\n        \n        # Build deployment\n        deployment = client.V1Deployment(\n            api_version=\"apps/v1\",\n            kind=\"Deployment\",\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                labels={\"app\": name},\n            ),\n            spec=deployment_spec,\n        )\n        \n        # Try to update first, then create\n        try:\n            apps_api.replace_namespaced_deployment(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                body=deployment,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Updated deployment {name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                # Create new deployment\n                apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment(\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                    body=deployment,\n                )\n                self.logger.debug(f\"Created deployment {name}\")\n            else:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to create deployment: {e}\")\n        \n        return {\"name\": name}\n```\n\n#### Create Service\n\n```python\n    def _create_service(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        port: int,\n        node_port: Optional[int],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Create or update NodePort Service resource.\n        \n        Args:\n            name: Service name\n            port: Target container port\n            node_port: Optional specific NodePort\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with service info including assigned node_port\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        core_api = k8s['core']\n        \n        # Build service spec\n        service_spec = client.V1ServiceSpec(\n            type=\"NodePort\",\n            selector={\"app\": name},\n            ports=[client.V1ServicePort(\n                port=port,\n                target_port=port,\n                node_port=node_port,\n            )],\n        )\n        \n        # Build service\n        service = client.V1Service(\n            api_version=\"v1\",\n            kind=\"Service\",\n            metadata=client.V1ObjectMeta(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                labels={\"app\": name},\n            ),\n            spec=service_spec,\n        )\n        \n        # Try to update first, then create\n        try:\n            core_api.replace_namespaced_service(\n                name=name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                body=service,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Updated service {name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                # Create new service\n                created = core_api.create_namespaced_service(\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                    body=service,\n                )\n                self.logger.debug(f\"Created service {name}\")\n                # Get assigned node port\n                node_port = created.spec.ports[0].node_port\n            else:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to create service: {e}\")\n        \n        # Get node port if not specified\n        if node_port is None:\n            svc = core_api.read_namespaced_service(name, self.namespace)\n            node_port = svc.spec.ports[0].node_port\n        \n        return {\"name\": name, \"node_port\": node_port}\n```\n\n#### Wait for Deployment\n\n```python\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(\n        self,\n        name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Wait for deployment to be ready.\n        \n        Args:\n            name: Deployment name\n            timeout: Maximum wait time in seconds\n            \n        Raises:\n            TimeoutError: If deployment doesn't become ready within timeout\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        apps_api = k8s['apps']\n        \n        start_time = time.time()\n        while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n            try:\n                deployment = apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n                    name=name,\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                )\n                \n                # Check status\n                status = deployment.status\n                if (status.updated_replicas == status.replicas and\n                    status.ready_replicas == status.replicas):\n                    self.logger.debug(f\"Deployment {name} is ready\")\n                    return\n                \n                self.logger.debug(\n                    f\"Waiting for deployment {name}: \"\n                    f\"{status.ready_replicas}/{status.replicas} ready\"\n                )\n                \n            except ApiException as e:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error checking deployment status: {e}\")\n            \n            time.sleep(5)\n        \n        raise TimeoutError(\n            f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\"\n        )\n```\n\n#### Get Status\n\n```python\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get deployment and service status.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name of the agent\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deployment and service status\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        apps_api = k8s['apps']\n        core_api = k8s['core']\n        \n        result = {\n            \"deployment\": None,\n            \"service\": None,\n        }\n        \n        # Get deployment status\n        try:\n            deployment = apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n                name=agent_name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n            )\n            result[\"deployment\"] = {\n                \"name\": deployment.metadata.name,\n                \"replicas\": deployment.spec.replicas,\n                \"ready_replicas\": deployment.status.ready_replicas or 0,\n                \"updated_replicas\": deployment.status.updated_replicas or 0,\n            }\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error getting deployment status: {e}\")\n        \n        # Get service status\n        try:\n            service = core_api.read_namespaced_service(\n                name=agent_name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n            )\n            result[\"service\"] = {\n                \"name\": service.metadata.name,\n                \"type\": service.spec.type,\n                \"cluster_ip\": service.spec.cluster_ip,\n                \"node_port\": service.spec.ports[0].node_port if service.spec.ports else None,\n            }\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error getting service status: {e}\")\n        \n        return result\n```\n\n#### Delete Agent\n\n```python\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Delete deployment and service resources.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name of the agent to delete\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deletion status\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        apps_api = k8s['apps']\n        core_api = k8s['core']\n        \n        result = {\n            \"status\": \"deleted\",\n            \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n            \"service_name\": agent_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n        }\n        \n        # Delete deployment\n        try:\n            apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment(\n                name=agent_name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted deployment {agent_name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting deployment: {e}\")\n        \n        # Delete service\n        try:\n            core_api.delete_namespaced_service(\n                name=agent_name,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted service {agent_name}\")\n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting service: {e}\")\n        \n        return result\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. AgentCubeProvider\n\nThe `AgentCubeProvider` class deploys agents using the AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    \"\"\"Provider for AgentRuntime CR deployments.\n    \n    Creates and manages AgentRuntime Custom Resources for deployment\n    to AgentCube-enabled Kubernetes clusters.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # CRD configuration\n    CRD_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    CRD_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n    CRD_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the AgentCube provider.\n        \n        Args:\n            namespace: Default namespace for resources\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging\n            kubeconfig: Path to kubeconfig file (optional)\n        \"\"\"\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.kubeconfig = kubeconfig\n        self.logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n        self._k8s_client = None\n        \n        if verbose:\n            self.logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n```\n\n#### Deploy Agent Runtime\n\n```python\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        session_timeout: str = \"15m\",\n        max_session_duration: str = \"8h\",\n        image_pull_secrets: Optional[list] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name for the agent\n            image_url: Container image URL\n            port: Container port\n            entrypoint: Optional entrypoint command\n            env_vars: Environment variables\n            workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n            router_url: Router URL\n            readiness_probe_path: Path for readiness probe\n            readiness_probe_port: Port for readiness probe\n            session_timeout: Session timeout duration\n            max_session_duration: Maximum session duration\n            image_pull_secrets: List of image pull secret names\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deployment info including:\n            - agent_id, agent_endpoint, status\n            - name, namespace\n            - workload_manager_url, router_url\n            \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If required URLs are missing\n            RuntimeError: If deployment fails\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n        \n        # Validate required URLs\n        if not workload_manager_url or not router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"AgentRuntime deployment requires both \"\n                \"workload_manager_url and router_url\"\n            )\n        \n        # Ensure namespace exists\n        self._ensure_namespace()\n        \n        # Build CR spec\n        cr_spec = self._build_agent_runtime_spec(\n            agent_name=agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=port,\n            entrypoint=entrypoint,\n            env_vars=env_vars,\n            workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n            router_url=router_url,\n            readiness_probe_path=readiness_probe_path,\n            readiness_probe_port=readiness_probe_port,\n            session_timeout=session_timeout,\n            max_session_duration=max_session_duration,\n            image_pull_secrets=image_pull_secrets,\n        )\n        \n        # Apply CR\n        result = self._apply_agent_runtime_cr(agent_name, cr_spec)\n        \n        # Add metadata to result\n        result.update({\n            \"agent_id\": agent_name,\n            \"agent_endpoint\": f\"{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{self.namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\",\n            \"workload_manager_url\": workload_manager_url,\n            \"router_url\": router_url,\n            \"status\": \"deployed\",\n        })\n        \n        self.logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime {agent_name} deployed successfully\")\n        return result\n```\n\n#### Build CR Spec\n\n```python\n    def _build_agent_runtime_spec(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str],\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n        workload_manager_url: str,\n        router_url: str,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str],\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int],\n        session_timeout: str,\n        max_session_duration: str,\n        image_pull_secrets: Optional[list],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Build AgentRuntime CR specification.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Dict with AgentRuntime spec\n        \"\"\"\n        # Build environment variables\n        env = []\n        if env_vars:\n            env.extend([{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in env_vars.items()])\n        \n        # Add required AgentCube env vars\n        env.extend([\n            {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n            {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n        ])\n        \n        # Build container spec\n        container = {\n            \"name\": agent_name,\n            \"image\": image_url,\n            \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n            \"env\": env,\n        }\n        \n        # Add entrypoint if provided\n        if entrypoint:\n            parts = entrypoint.split()\n            container[\"command\"] = [parts[0]] if parts else []\n            if len(parts) > 1:\n                container[\"args\"] = parts[1:]\n        \n        # Add readiness probe if configured\n        if readiness_probe_path:\n            container[\"readinessProbe\"] = {\n                \"httpGet\": {\n                    \"path\": readiness_probe_path,\n                    \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n                },\n                \"initialDelaySeconds\": 10,\n                \"periodSeconds\": 5,\n            }\n        \n        # Build pod template\n        pod_spec = {\n            \"containers\": [container],\n        }\n        \n        # Add image pull secrets\n        if image_pull_secrets:\n            pod_spec[\"imagePullSecrets\"] = [\n                {\"name\": secret} for secret in image_pull_secrets\n            ]\n        else:\n            # Default secret\n            pod_spec[\"imagePullSecrets\"] = [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]\n        \n        # Build AgentRuntime spec\n        spec = {\n            \"image\": image_url,\n            \"port\": port,\n            \"sessionTimeout\": session_timeout,\n            \"maxSessionDuration\": max_session_duration,\n            \"podTemplate\": {\n                \"spec\": pod_spec,\n            },\n        }\n        \n        return spec\n```\n\n#### Apply CR\n\n```python\n    def _apply_agent_runtime_cr(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        cr_spec: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Apply AgentRuntime CR using CustomObjectsApi.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name for the CR\n            cr_spec: CR specification\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with CR info\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        custom_api = k8s['custom']\n        \n        # Build CR body\n        cr_body = {\n            \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CRD_GROUP}/{self.CRD_VERSION}\",\n            \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"metadata\": {\n                \"name\": agent_name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n                \"labels\": {\"app\": agent_name},\n            },\n            \"spec\": cr_spec,\n        }\n        \n        # Try to get existing CR\n        try:\n            existing = custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n                version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n                name=agent_name,\n            )\n            \n            # Update existing CR\n            custom_api.replace_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n                version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n                name=agent_name,\n                body=cr_body,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Updated AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n            \n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                # Create new CR\n                custom_api.create_namespaced_custom_object(\n                    group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n                    version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n                    namespace=self.namespace,\n                    plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n                    body=cr_body,\n                )\n                self.logger.debug(f\"Created AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n            else:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n        \n        return {\"name\": agent_name, \"namespace\": self.namespace}\n```\n\n#### Get Status\n\n```python\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime CR status.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name of the AgentRuntime\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with CR status\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        custom_api = k8s['custom']\n        \n        try:\n            cr = custom_api.get_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n                version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n                name=agent_name,\n            )\n            \n            status = cr.get(\"status\", {})\n            return {\n                \"name\": agent_name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n                \"status\": status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n                \"agent_endpoint\": status.get(\"agentEndpoint\"),\n                \"conditions\": status.get(\"conditions\", []),\n            }\n            \n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status == 404:\n                return {\"name\": agent_name, \"status\": \"not_found\"}\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to get AgentRuntime status: {e}\")\n```\n\n#### Delete Agent\n\n```python\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Delete AgentRuntime CR.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name of the AgentRuntime to delete\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dict with deletion status\n        \"\"\"\n        k8s = self._get_k8s_client()\n        custom_api = k8s['custom']\n        \n        try:\n            custom_api.delete_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=self.CRD_GROUP,\n                version=self.CRD_VERSION,\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=self.CRD_PLURAL,\n                name=agent_name,\n            )\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Deleted AgentRuntime {agent_name}\")\n            \n        except ApiException as e:\n            if e.status != 404:\n                self.logger.warning(f\"Error deleting AgentRuntime: {e}\")\n        \n        return {\n            \"status\": \"deleted\",\n            \"name\": agent_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n        }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Models\n\n### KubernetesProvider Deployment Result\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `deployment_name` | `str` | Name of the Deployment resource |\n| `service_name` | `str` | Name of the Service resource |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Deployment namespace |\n| `replicas` | `int` | Number of pod replicas |\n| `container_port` | `int` | Container port exposed |\n| `node_port` | `int` | Assigned NodePort (30000-32767) |\n| `service_url` | `str` | Service access URL |\n| `status` | `str` | Deployment status (`\"deployed\"`) |\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Deployment Result\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `agent_id` | `str` | Agent identifier |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `str` | Agent invocation endpoint |\n| `name` | `str` | CR name |\n| `namespace` | `str` | CR namespace |\n| `status` | `str` | Deployment status (`\"deployed\"`) |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `str` | Workload Manager URL |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Router URL |\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Spec\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: {agent_name}\n  namespace: {namespace}\nspec:\n  image: {image_url}\n  port: {port}\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      imagePullSecrets:\n        - name: default-secret\n      containers:\n        - name: {agent_name}\n          image: {image_url}\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: {port}\n          env:\n            - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n              value: {workload_manager_url}\n            - name: ROUTER_URL\n              value: {router_url}\n          command: [{command}]\n          args: [{args}]\n          readinessProbe:\n            httpGet:\n              path: {readiness_probe_path}\n              port: {readiness_probe_port}\n            initialDelaySeconds: 10\n            periodSeconds: 5\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Exception | Description |\n|-------|-----------|-------------|\n| K8s Library Missing | `RuntimeError` | kubernetes package not installed |\n| K8s Config Failed | `RuntimeError` | Could not load kubeconfig |\n| Invalid NodePort | `ValueError` | Outside 30000-32767 range |\n| Missing URLs | `ValueError` | router_url or workload_manager_url missing |\n| Deployment Failed | `RuntimeError` | API error during deployment |\n| Timeout | `TimeoutError` | Deployment not ready within timeout |\n| CR Not Found | Returns dict | `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` |\n\n### Error Patterns\n\n**K8s Library Check:**\n```python\ntry:\n    from kubernetes import client, config\nexcept ImportError:\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Kubernetes client library not installed\")\n```\n\n**Config Loading:**\n```python\ntry:\n    config.load_kube_config()\nexcept Exception:\n    try:\n        config.load_incluster_config()\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to load K8s configuration: {e}\")\n```\n\n**API Error Handling:**\n```python\ntry:\n    api.create_namespaced_deployment(...)\nexcept ApiException as e:\n    if e.status == 404:\n        # Handle not found\n    else:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Deployment failed: {e}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used For |\n|----------|----------|\n| `KUBECONFIG` | Path to kubeconfig file |\n| `AGENTCUBE_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Default Workload Manager URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_ROUTER_URL` | Default Router URL |\n\n### Provider Parameters\n\n**KubernetesProvider:**\n- `namespace`: Target namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n- `verbose`: Enable debug logging (default: `False`)\n- `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n\n**AgentCubeProvider:**\n- `namespace`: Target namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n- `verbose`: Enable debug logging (default: `False`)\n- `kubeconfig`: Path to kubeconfig (optional)\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider tests**:\n   - `test_init` - Provider initialization\n   - `test_get_k8s_client_lazy` - Lazy loading\n   - `test_ensure_namespace_create` - Namespace creation\n   - `test_deploy_agent_success` - Successful deployment\n   - `test_deploy_agent_invalid_nodeport` - NodePort validation\n   - `test_wait_for_deployment_ready` - Readiness polling\n   - `test_wait_for_deployment_timeout` - Timeout handling\n   - `test_get_agent_status` - Status retrieval\n   - `test_delete_agent` - Resource deletion\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider tests**:\n   - `test_init` - Provider initialization\n   - `test_deploy_agent_runtime_success` - CR deployment\n   - `test_deploy_agent_runtime_missing_urls` - URL validation\n   - `test_build_agent_runtime_spec` - Spec building\n   - `test_apply_agent_runtime_cr` - CR application\n   - `test_get_agent_status` - CR status retrieval\n   - `test_delete_agent` - CR deletion\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Full Deploy Flow**:\n   - Initialize provider\n   - Deploy agent\n   - Verify resources created\n   - Check status\n   - Delete and cleanup\n\n2. **AgentRuntime CR Flow**:\n   - Deploy AgentRuntime\n   - Verify CR created\n   - Check status endpoint\n   - Delete CR\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Kubeconfig Security**:\n   - Respect kubeconfig file permissions\n   - Support explicit kubeconfig path\n   - No hardcoded credentials\n\n2. **RBAC Compliance**:\n   - Requires Deployment/Service CRUD permissions\n   - Requires AgentRuntime CRUD permissions (for AgentCubeProvider)\n   - Namespace-scoped operations\n\n3. **Secret Handling**:\n   - Image pull secrets referenced, not embedded\n   - Environment variables for sensitive URLs\n   - No credential logging\n\n4. **Resource Isolation**:\n   - Namespace isolation\n   - Label-based selectors\n   - Sanitized resource names\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Typical Duration | Notes |\n|-----------|------------------|-------|\n| Client Init | ~500ms | One-time per provider |\n| Deploy | ~2-5s | API calls + resource creation |\n| Wait Ready | ~10-60s | Depends on image pull |\n| Get Status | ~100ms | Single API call |\n| Delete | ~1-2s | Resource cleanup |\n\n### Optimization Strategies\n\n1. **Lazy Client**: K8s client initialized once, cached\n2. **Create-or-Update**: Single code path for both operations\n3. **Timeout Config**: Configurable timeouts\n4. **Graceful Degradation**: 404 errors handled gracefully\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes Python client |\n| `urllib3` | (dependency) | HTTP client |\n| `pyyaml` | (dependency) | YAML parsing |\n\n### Python Requirements\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\", ...]\ntest = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\", ...]\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](../../cli-toolkit/design.md) - Overall CLI design\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](../../cli-toolkit/spec.md) - CLI specification\n- [deployment/client-go.md](../../deployment/client-go.md) - AgentRuntime CR API\n- [Kubernetes Python Client](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python) - Official docs\n- [Kubernetes Deployment](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/) - K8s concepts\n- [Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/) - CRDs\n- AR-025 — MetadataService (prerequisite)\n- AR-020-024 — CLI Commands (use providers)\n\n---\n\n*AR-026 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/design.md","time":{"start":1775900238952,"end":1775900239035}}}}
